vocabulary.definition: in good health, especially because of regular physical exercise
vocabulary.example: She goes to the gym every day to stay fit.

vocabulary.definition: a mythical island mentioned in Plato's dialogues as the home of an advanced civilization
vocabulary.example: They were exploring the depths of the ocean in search of the lost city of Atlantis.

vocabulary.definition: to stumble or fall over something
vocabulary.example: She tripped over a rock while hiking in the mountains.

vocabulary.definition: having an edge or point that is able to cut or pierce something
vocabulary.example: Be careful with that knife, it's very sharp.

vocabulary.definition: the standard of something as measured against other things of a similar kind; the degree of excellence of something
vocabulary.example: The hotel offers high-quality services to its guests.

vocabulary.definition: a place regarded in various religions as a spiritual realm of evil and suffering, often depicted as the abode of the devil and the demons
vocabulary.example: The protagonist in the story feared he would end up in hell if he didn't repent.
